gomodel:SYNGO_522  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3E,F\nShank2 is associated with the PSD\nLiteral\n\"labeling is relatively weak in dendrites (d), enhanced toward dendritic spines (sp), and very strong at PSDs (arrowheads, arrows). \"\nFig 4\nShank2 is synaptically localized\nLiteral\n\"Figure 4A,B illustrates the punctate distribution and close apposition of ProSAP1-immunoreactive structures and the presynaptic cytomatrix protein Bassoon. The virtually complementary localization of ProSAP1 and the synap- tic vesicle protein synaptophysin or Bassoon at mossy fiber bou- tons of the CA3 region can be seen in Figure 4C,D.\". Experimental description: Electron microscopy is performed in rat brain's slices\nLiteral from M&M\n\"Electron microscopy was performed using vibratome sections (50 m) from rat brains fixed by perfusion with Karnowsky's solution,\"\nExperiment of immunohistochemistry are made in rat.\nLiteral from M&M\n\"Immunocytochemical staining was performed using 7 m microtome sections from rat brains\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_522" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

